Happy Sunday friends!💕 It’s day 2 of #YogiRefresh and our topic today is physical well-being, with any arm balance for the accompanying pose.

My dedication to my asana practice has undoubtedly been a key aspect of my growth in the last year, in all areas of my life. I took 4-5 classes a week when I bought an unlimited pass my first month practicing. When that pass ran out, I promised myself I’d get on my mat at home every single day. And except for those days that my stomach problems made it a little too difficult, I did. But I always felt guilty on those days that I couldn’t. I felt like I should flow, and sometimes tried to force it with terribly uncomfortable results.

I think part of our practice is also learning when not to. Sometimes our bodies need a break. Sometimes we just need a day, and that’s more than ok. Being on my mat is one of my absolute favourite things, it’s my sacred space. But I’m learning not to beat myself up for the days I listen to my body telling me to slow down, or even to stop.

